vectorData.altText: 4. The dural venous sinus that lies in the attached edge of the falx cerebri is the ___________ _____________ sinus.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
That’s right!  The superior sagittal sinus is attached to the superior edge of the falx cerebri.

Recall that the dural venous sinuses are located along the line of attachment of the dural reflections, that they receive blood from the cerebral veins, and that they empty into the internal jugular veins at the jugular foramen. You will now begin to trace the dural venous sinuses.

Identify the inferior sagittal sinus in the free (inferior) edge of the falx cerebri. 
Identify the continuation of the inferior sagittal sinus as the straight sinus along the line of attachment of the falx cerebri with the tentorium cerebelli. 
Identify the confluence of sinuses, the point at which the straight sinus meets the superior sagittal sinus.
